Description
-----------

You can find the library (SW@P) in the folder public/javascripts/swap/. The system that has been built on top of it is available in the folder public/javascripts/credsystem/. This system requires some parameters and specifications that have been put in resources/.

server/ contains the files required by the server to operate.

views/ contains the files required by the client to model the interaction with the users.


Execution
---------

First of all, to run the application locally, you should have Node.JS installed on your machine.

To run the server, simply enter

  node swap.js

at the prompt.

Now you can start playing with the tool.


